The paper deals with geometric graphs and their connectivity properties, which are typical topics in computational geometry (cs.CG). The study of graph augmentation is also a common topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the existence and non-existence of certain types of graphs, which is related to the study of extremal graph theory, a subfield of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The connectivity properties of graphs are also relevant to the study of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the construction of graphs with certain properties, which is a topic in computational and combinatorial optimization (cs.SI).
